description: Sorry for the poor quality photos. Flew low overhead in direct flight from west to east from ridgeline to ridgeline across lake. Initially thought to be a large buteo or even an eagle by size and broad wings but as the bird approached it was clear it was a very large accipiter with relatively long banded black and gray tail with whitish tail tip but broad wings and deep chest, wings held with a slight crook, medium gray on back, pale below. From Cooper's by paler grayer coloration, broader wings and relatively smaller-appearing head (otherwise did not see head details due to angle) in proportion to body and tail; also habitat. From Buteos by long banded tail and structure.

description: In the spring of 2003 at Valley View site in Yosemite Valley my wife saw a female Harlequin Duck.  None had been seen in the valley for apparently 80 years.  The following March we saw a pair from Pohono bridge. Later, park naturalists found the female was raising some young.  We found her each spring through 2006 but no nesting was noted.  We have not seen a Harlequin there since.
